1. The Date and Time API(JSR 310) providing a comprehensive set of classes to handle date,time and duration operations.

2. JSR 310 stands for "Java Specification Request 310", and it is the formal request to add the Date and Time API to the
   Java Standard Edition(Java SE).

3. It is the solution to problems in java.util.Date and java.util.Calender classes.

4. The classes in the Date and Time API are immutable , meaning their values can't be changed once created , ensuring
    thread safety in multi-threaded environments.

5. The API is part of the java.time package and includes classes such as LocalDate, LocalTime, LocalDateTime
    ZonedDateTime, Duration, Period and more.
